outputs.output_descr:
To guarantee successful implementation of the Government's national development strategy, the Medium Term Plan, and accordingly, an economically stable and prosperous Zimbabwe, there is urgent need to strengthen capacity in a number of institutions and sectors at different levels. Strengthening of aid coordination mechanisms and harmonization of practices is crucial to ensure government leadership and ownership of development process, to build strong partnerships with the international community and to strengthen accountability mechanisms for both public and donor resources.
The Strengthened National Capacities for Public Finance, Aid and Debt Management Project will through a comprehensive approach, under leadership of the Government of Zimbabwe, work towards strengthening these institutions and mechanisms and supporting the country's longer term development. Specifically, the Project aims to deliver on the following key results: 
•	Integrated Public Finance Management Systems fully functional;
•	Aid and Development results mechanism revamped and integrated into national development processes;
•	Debt management capacity strengthened;
•	Programme management implementation capacities strengthened.
